In 2005, while working for the original McGill family business The North Rocks Greenery, Jon recognised an opportunity. He took on his first Garden Maintenance job armed with just a pair of secateurs, before growing into a thriving local business and expanding to Landscaping.

While under The North Rocks Greenery the business primarily serviced the Hills district of Sydney. The McGill family was then forced to re-brand that side of the business following the sale of the Nursery. Despite many challenges, that change has acted as a catalyst for rapid growth.

Under it's new name, Looking Up Landscapes, the business has moved away from Garden Maintenance to fully Certified Landscaping services and has shifted their area of work to encompass the Central Coast, Lake Macquarie area, the Hunter Valley and Newcastle.
